cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper proposes a domain adaptation approach for object detection using style transfer and pseudo labelling. The main focus is on computer vision (CV) and machine learning (LG) techniques for object detection, which suggests that cs.CV and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves some artificial intelligence (AI) techniques for adapting the classifiers, which makes cs.AI a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper evaluates the approach using a benchmark dataset, which suggests that multimedia (MM) and information retrieval (IR) could also be relevant sub-categories.
